                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client is experiencing diarrhea. The nurse reviews the client's \"as needed\" (PRN) medication prescription sheet and would plan to administer which medication for this problem?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nLoperamide is an antidiarrheal agent. It inhibits peristalsis in the intestinal wall and inhibits intestinal secretion so that the number of stools and water content are decreased. Psyllium, bisacodyl, and sennosides are laxatives.",
